## Naming your captures

Session labels follow `{topic}_{prompt_id}_{thread_state}` and auto-split
into `topic`, `prompt_id`, `thread_state` columns in the data.

| segment | pattern | example |
|---|---|---|
| `topic` | any text | `medium`, `elections` |
| `prompt_id` | `p0` or `m1`, `m2`… | `p0`, `m1` |
| `thread_state` | `cold` / `warm` | appended automatically in Longitudinal mode from Prompt condition (isolated/initial → cold, follow-up → warm) |

Examples: `medium_p0_cold` · `medium_p0_warm` ·
`elections_case01` (Comparative — no cold/warm needed).

---

## What you get in the data

Each row is one cited source, with columns including: `rank`, `capture_id`,
`capture_date`, `platform`, `capture_mode`, `prompt_condition`,
`search_condition`, `prompt_framing`, `session_label`, `note`, `url`,
`clean_url`, `redirect_url`, `hostname`, `domain`, `title`, `description`.
`prompt_condition` is filled only in longitudinal rows and `prompt_framing`
only in comparative rows — the empty column marks the other design.

